\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {33}{\ignorespaces Impact ranking of the top 15 nuisance parameters on the signal strength \(\mitmu \) for the NN score approach on Asimov data. The horizontal bars show the \(\mitDelta \mitmu \) impact of each nuisance parameter when varied up (blue) and down (orange). The four shape systematics (tau energy scale, muon energy scale, MET unclustered energy, jet energy scale) are the leading uncertainties, followed by normalization systematics for trigger efficiency, luminosity, and background normalizations.\relax }}{38}{figure.caption.72}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:impact-ranking}{{33}{38}{Impact ranking of the top 15 nuisance parameters on the signal strength \(\mu \) for the NN score approach on Asimov data. The horizontal bars show the \(\Delta \mu \) impact of each nuisance parameter when varied up (blue) and down (orange). The four shape systematics (tau energy scale, muon energy scale, MET unclustered energy, jet energy scale) are the leading uncertainties, followed by normalization systematics for trigger efficiency, luminosity, and background normalizations.\relax }{figure.caption.72}{}}
